1.00	Gasterias	Gasteria	Gasteria is a genus of succulent plants native to South Africa. Closely related genera include Aloe and Haworthia. The genus is named for its stomach-shaped flowers and is part of the family Xanthorrhoeaceae, subfamily Asphodeloideae. Common names include cow-tongue cactus, lawyer's tongue, mother-in-law's tongue, ox-tongue.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Gasteria_pillansii_var_pillansii_1.jpg/220px-Gasteria_pillansii_var_pillansii_1.jpg
